properties.name: Advice
properties.location: the Sevens Creek at Kialla West
properties.webBody:
This is a Final Minor Flood Warning for the Sevens Creek at Kialla West. 

Minor flooding has eased and river levels are falling along the Seven and Castle Creeks downstream of Euroa.

No significant rainfall has been recorded in the catchment since 9 am Saturday. No widespread significant rainfall is expected for the next few days.

Seven Creeks downstream of Euroa:
Flood levels are easing along the Seven Creeks downstream of Euroa.

The Seven Creeks at Kialla West recorded a moderate flood peak of 5.43 metres during Saturday morning. The flood level fell below the moderate flood level (5.00 metres) during Saturday evening and the minor flood level (4.50 metres) during Sunday morning. 

The Seven Creeks at Kialla West is currently at 4.37 metres and steady. The Seven Creeks at Kialla West will remain below the minor flood level (4.50 m).

The threat of flooding is reduced. Stay informed - monitor your local conditions and beware of hazards remaining in the warning area.
What you should do:

  • Be prepared to act if your situation changes.
  • Floodwater is dangerous - never enter floodwater.
  • Drive slowly, obey all roadblocks and never drive through floodwaters.

If your home or business has been flooded:
  • Check for building damage before you enter.
  • Have all electrical and gas equipment professionally tested before use.
  • Clean and dry out the building as soon as possible.

Call Triple Zero (000) in a life threatening emergency. For emergency assistance from the SES call 132 500.
Impacts in your area: 
  • Damage to roads and buildings caused by flooding may still exist in your area. 
  • Caravan parks and camping grounds may be flooded.
This message was issued by State Emergency Service.

This will be the last warning for this flood. 

Use multiple sources to stay informed:
  • www.emergency.vic.gov.au
  • VicEmergency Hotline - freecall 1800 226 226
  • VicEmergency app
  • Facebook or Twitter (#vicfloods)
  • Tune in to ABC Local Radio, commercial and designated community radio stations, or Sky News TV.

Accessibility:
The following services can help you, or someone you know, access information during an emergency.
  • To access this information in other languages call the Translating and Interpreting Service on 131 450 (freecall) and ask them to call VicEmergency Hotline.
  • If you are deaf, hard of hearing, or have a speech/communication impairment contact National Relay Service on 1800 555 677 and ask them to call the VicEmergency Hotline.

No significant rainfall has been recorded in the catchment in the 24 hours to 9 am Sunday, and no further significant rainfall is expected.

River levels will remain elevated for the next few days, however the Broken River at Orrvale is expected to remain below the minor flood level (6.80 m).

Kiewa River downstream of Mongans Bridge:
Minor flooding is continuing along the Kiewa River downstream of Mongans Bridge.

The Kiewa River at Kiewa (Main Stream) is currently at 3.35 metres and steady, with minor flooding. 
The Kiewa River at Kiewa (Main Stream) is likely to remain above the minor flood level (3.30 m) during Sunday and into Monday.

The Kiewa River at Bandiana is currently at 2.90 metres and steady, with minor flooding. The Kiewa River at Bandiana is likely to remain above the minor flood level (2.80 m) during Sunday and into Monday.

This Minor Flood Warning is being issued for the Ovens River at Wangaratta.

MINOR FLOODING EASING SLOWLY ALONG THE OVENS RIVER AT WANGARATTA  BRIDGE

Flood levels eased just below the moderate flood level at Wangaratta and Docker Rd Bridge during Saturday. Flood levels continue easing along the Ovens River upstream of Wangaratta.

No significant rainfall has been recorded since 9:00 am Saturday. No widespread significant rainfall is expected for the new few days.

Ovens River downstream of Rocky Point:
Flooding is easing along the Ovens River, with minor flooding continuing at Wangaratta. 
The Ovens River at Wangaratta fell below the moderate flood level (12.40 metres) overnight Saturday. The river level is currently at 12.31 metres and steady, with minor flooding. The Ovens River at Wangaratta is likely to remain above the minor flood level (11.90 m) during Sunday and into Monday.

Stay informed - monitor your local conditions and remain alert.
What you should do: 

  • Be prepared to act if your situation changes.
  • You should stay informed by listening to emergency broadcasters and monitoring warnings.
  • Floodwater is toxic - never play or swim in floodwater.
  • Floodwater is dangerous - never drive, walk or ride through floodwater.
Impacts in your area: 

  • High river levels and potential flooding in areas close to rivers and streams.
  • Caravan parks and camping grounds may be flooded.
  • Wangaratta's Apex Park in low lying areas will be flooded. 
  • Low lying car parks at: Sydney Beach Bickerton Street Baker Street Boat Ramp (off Templeton Street) Northern Beaches close. 
  • Bike and shared paths around the Rivers will remain closed.
  • Local roads may be closed and low bridges may be underwater.
This message was issued by State Emergency Service.

The next update is expected by 12/06/2023 11:00 am or as the situation changes.
